The  Bank of Japan  will announce
results of a policy meeting. The yen fell against all major
currencies yesterday, reflecting the view that the central bank
will be forced to keep  interest rates  low as the nation recovers
from the March 11 earthquake and tsunami.  WHAT TO WATCH
*Bank of Japan policy announcement, time unspecified
*Bank of Japan Governor Shirakawa briefing, 3:30 pm.
*Fast Retailing (9983 JP) reports first-half earnings and
 provides a full-year forecast update. The retailer currently
 forecasts full-year net income of 51 billion yen. 3:01 pm
*Seven & I (3382 JP) earnings, 3 pm  ECONOMY
*Bank of Japan policy announcement, time unspecified
*Bank of Japan Governor Shirakawa briefing, 3:30 pm
*Foreign exchange reserves as of March, 8:50 am
*International transactions in securities, weekly
*Tokyo office vacancies for March, 11 am  GOVERNMENT
